condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :FA. Sch. 2, Sect. II, B. 5 & all PAs Sched, Sect. III, B.4 | Description :Except otherwise agreed, the P.I.E.and the selected Water Service Providers must pay cash dividends only out of net income and only is such payment will not lowertheir current ration below 1.2. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :FA. Sche. 2, Sect. I B | Description :A Subsidiary Agreement has been executed on behalf of the Recipient andeach P.I.E. | Due Date :21-Sep-2012

Finance Agreement :FA. Sche. 2, Sect. I C 1 | Description :Not later than August 31, 2012, or any other date agreed with theAssociation, each P.I.E. shall enter into an Implementation Agreement with the Water Services Board for which the P.I.E. willimplement drought mitigation measures | Due Date :31-Aug-2012
Finance Agreement :FA. Sche. 2, Sect. I E | Description :The Recipient has updated the Project Implementation Manual | Due Date:21-Sep-2012

Finance Agreement :FA. Sche. 2, Sect. I, B.3 | Description :The transfer of the management and operations of water services inaccordance with the Transfer Plan by the due date or other date agreed with IDA | Due Date :30-Jun-2008

Finance Agreement :FA. Sche. 2, Sect. I, B.4 | Description :Budgetary allocations for infrastructure devt, and WSS in the districtslocated in the Proj. Implementing Entities' (P.I.E.) Service Areas is indicated in its budget and channeled through the P.I.E. |Due Date :30-Jun-2008

Finance Agreement :FA. Sche. 2, Sect. II, B.5 | Description :Except otherwise agreed, the P.I.E. and the selected Water ServiceProviders must achieve a positive net income, excluding depreciation and amortization charges, by the end of the proj. | Due Date:31-Dec-2019
